716668f-a.title: Manhattan: Bennett Avenue - 189th Street (West)
716668f-a.text:
Bennett Avenue, west side, between West 189th and 190th Streets, showing the old Niss Cornell Cottage. On top of the hiil is the
George Grey Harnard Studio.
E. P. Ghrysuie  Aprit, 1923

716669f-b.title: Manhattan: Bennett Avenue - 189th Street (West)
716669f-b.text:
Bennett Ave., north from West 189th Street, showing on the west side of the avenue,the Evangelical Lutheran Church of Our Saviours Atonement. The apartment house appearing on the right is the 6-story Champlain Arms, No. 165, and located at the N.E. corner of these two thoroughfares. In the background are two 2-story private dwellings that bear Nos. 218 and 220 and are at the head of 190 th
Street.
November 23, 1930.
P. L. Sperr.

716670f-b.title: Manhattan: Bennett Avenue - 189th Street (West)
716670f-b.text:
Bennett Ave., north from a point midway between West 189th and 190th Streets, showing on the west side two 2-story homes and on the east side, a row of apartment houses. The structures are north of. 190th Street and bear Nos. 218-220 and 209 to 237 respectively. No. 2 of this set of 3 views shows the former, while No. 3, the latter.
November 23, 1930.
P. L. Sperr.
